HEADWORD: antitussive
<hw>antitussive</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a medicament used to
suppress or relieve coughing; an antitussive substance.</def>
<note>Codeine is one such commonly used <ex>antitussive</ex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

